The paper deals with the construction of randomness-efficient curve samplers, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The construction involves several components, including iterated sampling and list-recoverable codes, which are techniques commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and error-correcting codes (cs.CR, cs.DM).
